<h2>About Me</h2>
<p>I am currently a Ph.D candidate at the Department of Electrical and Computer Engineering, Missouri University of Science and Technology, USA. 
I received my B.Sc. and M.Sc degrees in Electrical Engineering from <a href="https://web.uettaxila.edu.pk/">University of Engineering and Technology (UET) Taxila, Pakistan</a> respectively in 2012 and 2017. I also received 
a second M.Sc. degree in Nuclear Engineering from <a href="http://www.pieas.edu.pk/">Pakistan Institute of Engineering and Applied Sciences (PIEAS)</a> in 2015. I'm a recipient of the <a href="https://econnection.mst.edu/2021/09/paper-on-fast-charging-stations-named-best-conference-paper/"><i>Best Conference Paper Award</i></a> 
and the <a href="https://econnection.mst.edu/2021/10/ph-d-student-earns-second-place-in-global-poster-contest/"><i>Second Prize</i></a> in the graduate poster competition at the IEEE PES General Meeting, USA 2021. My current research interests are optimal siting, sizing, operation and control 
of <a href="https://news.mst.edu/2018/10/missouri-st-researchers-win-multimillion-dollar-grant-to-build-fast-charging-stations-for-electric-cars/">Extreme Fast Charging (XFC) Stations</a> and Superchargers for electric vehicles. I am also interested in applying machine learning and AI methods in power and energy systems.  </p>
<h2>News</h2>
<ul>
<li><p>[04-22-2022] I won the <i>First Place</i> with $200 cash prize in the <a href="https://grad.mst.edu/events/graduatefellowspostersession/">2022 Missouri S&amp;T Graduate Poster Contest</a>, out of 28 contestants (poster title &ldquo;Multi-layered Framework for Energy Management of Extreme Fast Charging Stations for Electric Vehicles&rdquo;).</p>
</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><p>[02-12-2022] Our paper titled “Sizing battery energy storage and PV system in an extreme fast charging station considering uncertainties and battery degradation” got accepted 
in the <i>Applied Energy</i>. <a href="https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S030626192200201X">[Link]</a> <a href="https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Waqas-Ur-Rehman-3/publication/358569775_Sizing_Battery_Energy_Storage_and_PV_System_in_an_Extreme_Fast_Charging_Station_Considering_Uncertainties_and_Battery_Degradation/links/62137aff4be28e145ca7299b/Sizing-Battery-Energy-Storage-and-PV-System-in-an-Extreme-Fast-Charging-Station-Considering-Uncertainties-and-Battery-Degradation.pdf">[PDF]</a> </p>
